headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 27 points and made seven 3-pointers, and the Charlotte Hornets routed the Houston Rockets 123-99 on Monday night for their second straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier scores 27, Hornets rout depleted Rockets 123-99

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 35 points, Zach LaVine added 30 and the Chicago Bulls won their fourth straight game, beating the short-handed Atlanta Hawks 130-118 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, LaVine, Vucevic power Bulls past Hawks 130-118

headlines.description: — Jaylen Nowell scored 29 points and Nathan Knight added 20 points and 11 rebounds, leading the short-handed Minnesota Timberwolves to a 108-103 win over the Boston Celtics on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed T-Wolves snap 2-game skid, beat Celtics 108-103

events.name: Utah Jazz at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson provided Utah with a needed emotional lift, which he was able to maintain despite a fan trying to shake him.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson, Gobert lead Jazz by Spurs 110-104 without Mitchell

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had one thing on his mind after Devin Booker's 3-pointer with 5 seconds left gave the Phoenix Suns their first lead since early in the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores in final second, Grizzlies edge Suns 114-113

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis had a season-high 34 points and nine rebounds, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Portland Trail Blazers 132-117 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis powers Mavericks past Trail Blazers 132-117

headlines.description: — So much for feeling his way back after being out two weeks in the NBA's health and safety protocols. James Harden sure looks all the way back.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden scores 39, Nets beat Clippers 124-108 for LA sweep
